    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisite</strong><em><strong>:</strong> Dragonid</em></p><p>Instead of exhaling destructive energy, you can expend a use of your Breath Weapon trait to roar, forcing each creature of your choice within 30 feet of you to make a Wisdom saving throw (DC 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier). A target automatically succeeds on the save if it can't hear or see you. On a failed save, a target becomes frightened of you for 1 minute. If the frightened target takes any damage, it can repeat the saving throw, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p><section id=\"secret-dengckYs2cfJbdZ0\" class=\"secret\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>Upon selecting this feat, you should update the \"Item Uses\" selection of the \"Feature Usage\" section on the \"Details\" tab to point to your Breath Weapon feature so that it consumes those charges.</p></section>",
